description:
A long-awaited update for my very own blue screen simulator! This video exists, because so many people saw the first one and I didn't think the original was good enough. So this is version 2.0!

This video showcases some of the new features.

If you have already downloaded the first version of BSSP, you can upgrade to version 2.0 after opening that version and clicking "Yes" on the update prompt. If you do not have BSSP 1.x, you can download it from my Github repository under the "releases" section, i.e. from this link: https://github.com/MarkusMaal/BlueScreenSimulatorPlus .

Music:
Declan DP - Blue
Underwaterbeats - Undelete!
ACME - Mental Deliverance
Chris Zabriskie - Out of The Skies Under The Earth
Geographer - Weirder Stuff
Malmen - Heartbleed

Website: https://markustegelane.eu
Random video: https://markustegelane.eu/markustegelane/random/?c=mt

comments.text:
Version 2.121 released!
What's new
* CRITICAL 2.121 PATCH *
* Fixed save configurations button not working
* Version from GitHub contains dots in place of spaces, which the updated update manager should be able to handle

* 2.12 changelog *
+ You can now close blue screens by pressing Escape or F7, in addition to Alt+F4
* Updated to .NET 4.8
* Improved blue screen generation speed
* Changed the name of the executable to "Blue screen simulator plus.exe"
* Automatically switch to night mode if Windows dark mode is active
* Changed default update server to markustegelane.eu
* Minor bug fixes

Upgrade from a previous version
Open any version of blue screen simulator plus. If you are using a 1.x version, you'll automatically be prompted that a new version is available. If not, go to settings and check for updates. If you are using 2.x or later, you may need to change your update server. Select one, which says "markustegelane.tk" and if it isn't listed, select a custom server and set it to "http://markustegelane.tk/app ". Then you can check for updates. Select "Yes" to start the update process.

Download if you don't have a previous version installed:
Download the .exe from here: https://github.com/MarkusMaal/BlueScreenSimulatorPlus/releases/tag/2.121

comments.text: How do we install it i only have the zip what's next?!?!?
comments.author: @dylgummy2257

comments.text:
1. Extract the ZIP archive to a location you can find
2. Go to the folder where you extracted the files
3. Right click on "UltimateBlueScreenSimulator" exe file
4. Select "Properties"
5. Click "Unblock"
6. Click "OK"
7. Double click on "UltimateBlueScreenSimulator" exe file
8. Read the message box that appeared carefully and click "Yes"
9. Enjoy :)

There's no install wizard, just put the files in a folder on either your internal or any external drive.

comments.text: Windows Defender warns about every program that isn't signed. I don't want to go through Microsoft, just for a hobby project. That being said, signing doesn't really tell much tough, since I've seen many PUPs that were officially signed (and Windows Defender didn't warn about those at all). I actually had a signed installer UAC trap me once (essentially it was stuck displaying the UAC prompt until I clicked Yes, clicking No caused it to appear again).
